  "prompt": "What 6/9 mean in eyesight?",
  "response": "In eyesight measurement, 6/9 refers to visual acuity, which indicates how well a person can see at a specific distance compared to what is considered \"normal\" vision.\n\nHere's a breakdown:\n- 6/9 means that at 6 meters, you can see what a person with normal vision can see at 9 meters\n- This is considered slightly below standard vision (which is 6/6)\n- In the U.S. system, this would be equivalent to 20/30 vision\n- It indicates mild visual impairment, but not severe enough to require significant correction in most cases\n\nPeople with 6/9 vision may need glasses or contact lenses to improve their visual clarity, depending on individual circumstances and specific vision needs.",
